fortresses of the Rhine reflect major changes in Germany and Europe during the nineteenth and early twentieth centuries. Taylor begins The Castles of the Rhine with a synopsis of the major political, social and intellectual changes that influenced castle rebuilding in the nineteenth century. He then focuses on selected castles, describing their turbulent histories from the time of their original construction, through their destruction or decay, to their rediscovery in the 1800s and their continued preservation today. Reading this book is equivalent to looking at history though a romantic-nationalist kaleidoscope. Amply illustrated with maps and photographs, The Castles of the Rhine is a wonderful companion for anyone with dreams or experience of journeying along the Rhine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchitecturezGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aArchitecturezGermanyy19th century. 0aCastlesxConservation and restorationzRhine River Valley. 0aCastlesxReconstructionxGermanyxRhineland. 0aCastlesxReconstructionzGermanyzRhineland. 0aGothic revival (Architecture)zGermany. 0aGothic revival (Architecture)zRhine River Valley. 0aNationalism and architecturexGermanyxRhineland. 0aNationalism and architecturezGermanyzRhineland. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920585740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889205857423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889205857/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alle